---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro"
---

<Layout
  title="Botyoo for Coaches & Experts - Fill Your Calendar From Instagram"
  description="Turn followers into qualified leads, booked calls, and paying clients, without spending hours in your Instagram inbox."
>
  <main class="pt-28 pb-28">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6">

      {/* Hero */}
      <section class="py-12 border-b border-border">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-foreground mb-3">
          For Coaches & Experts
        </p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground max-w-2xl leading-tight">
          Fill your calendar from Instagram, without the DM grind.
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-muted-foreground max-w-xl leading-relaxed">
          Turn followers into qualified leads, booked calls, and paying clients, without spending hours in your Instagram inbox.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <a
            href="https://app.botyoo.com/dashboard"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-foreground text-background px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-foreground/90 transition-colors"
          >
            Get started free
          </a>
          <a
            href="/pricing"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card text-foreground px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-muted/50 transition-colors"
          >
            See pricing
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      {/* How it works */}
      <section class="py-14 border-b border-border">
        <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-foreground mb-12">
          How it works
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-20">

          {/* Step 1 */}
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
            <div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                <span class="flex items-center justify-center size-8 rounded-full bg-foreground/10 text-foreground text-sm font-bold">1</span>
                <span class="text-xs font-medium text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wide">Capture</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-3">Capture leads from every post</h3>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                A comment or story reply kicks off a DM flow that collects their email and delivers your lead magnet automatically. No manual follow-up needed, your funnel starts the moment they engage.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-card/80 ring-1 ring-foreground/10 rounded-2xl p-6">
              <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground mb-4">Flow triggered by comment</p>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                <div class="bg-foreground/5 rounded-lg p-3 text-xs text-foreground/80">
                  Comment <strong>"CLARITY"</strong> and I'll DM you my free 5-step framework for signing your first coaching client 👇
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground pt-1">
                  <div class="flex -space-x-1.5">
                    <div class="size-5 rounded-full bg-foreground/10 ring-1 ring-background flex items-center justify-center text-foreground/60 text-[9px]">JT</div>
                    <div class="size-5 rounded-full bg-foreground/10 ring-1 ring-background flex items-center justify-center text-foreground/60 text-[9px]">ML</div>
                    <div class="size-5 rounded-full bg-foreground/10 ring-1 ring-background flex items-center justify-center text-foreground/60 text-[9px]">AK</div>
                  </div>
                  <span>14 people triggered this flow today</span>
                </div>
                <div class="border-t border-foreground/10 pt-3 space-y-2">
                  <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs">
                    <div class="size-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary"></div>
                    <span class="text-muted-foreground">Email collected from 9 of 14</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs">
                    <div class="size-1.5 rounded-full bg-foreground/30"></div>
                    <span class="text-muted-foreground">3 clicked booking link</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          {/* Step 2 */}
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
            <div class="md:order-2">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                <span class="flex items-center justify-center size-8 rounded-full bg-foreground/10 text-foreground text-sm font-bold">2</span>
                <span class="text-xs font-medium text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wide">Qualify</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-3">Qualify before they reach your calendar</h3>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                A short DM exchange filters serious prospects from tire-kickers. Your booking link only goes to people who answer the right way, so every call on your calendar has a real chance of converting.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-card/80 ring-1 ring-foreground/10 rounded-2xl p-6 md:order-1">
              <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground mb-4">Qualification DM flow</p>
              <div class="space-y-3 text-xs">
                <div class="flex gap-2">
                  <div class="size-6 rounded-full bg-foreground/10 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-0.5 text-foreground/70 text-[9px]">YC</div>
                  <div class="bg-foreground/5 rounded-lg rounded-tl-none p-2.5 text-muted-foreground">
                    Quick question, what's your biggest challenge with getting clients right now?
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-2 justify-end">
                  <div class="bg-foreground/10 rounded-lg rounded-tr-none p-2.5 text-foreground">
                    I have the skills but no system for finding people consistently
                  </div>
                  <div class="size-6 rounded-full bg-foreground/10 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-0.5 text-foreground/70 text-[9px]">L</div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-2">
                  <div class="size-6 rounded-full bg-foreground/10 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-0.5 text-foreground/70 text-[9px]">YC</div>
                  <div class="bg-foreground/5 rounded-lg rounded-tl-none p-2.5 text-muted-foreground">
                    That's exactly what we fix. Here's a link to book a free 20-min strategy call 👇<br/>
                    <span class="text-primary underline">calendly.com/yourcoach/strategy</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          {/* Step 3 */}
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
            <div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                <span class="flex items-center justify-center size-8 rounded-full bg-foreground/10 text-foreground text-sm font-bold">3</span>
                <span class="text-xs font-medium text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wide">Nurture</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-3">Nurture the rest automatically</h3>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                Not everyone books right away. Follow-up sequences re-engage cold leads with value touches, a tip, a case study, a gentle check-in, before presenting a softer next step. Stay top of mind without lifting a finger.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-card/80 ring-1 ring-foreground/10 rounded-2xl p-6">
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-foreground mb-4">Nurture sequence, cold leads</p>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg bg-foreground/5">
                  <span class="text-xs text-muted-foreground w-14 shrink-0 pt-0.5">Day 3</span>
                  <p class="text-muted-foreground text-xs">"Here's how one of my clients went from 0 → 3 paying clients in 6 weeks 🧵"</p>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg bg-foreground/5">
                  <span class="text-xs text-muted-foreground w-14 shrink-0 pt-0.5">Day 7</span>
                  <p class="text-muted-foreground text-xs">"No pressure, just want to check if you had any questions about the framework I sent"</p>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg bg-foreground/5">
                  <span class="text-xs text-muted-foreground w-14 shrink-0 pt-0.5">Day 14</span>
                  <p class="text-muted-foreground text-xs">"I have 2 spots opening up next month. Want me to send you details?"</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      {/* Use Cases */}
      <section class="py-14 border-b border-border">
        <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-foreground mb-8">
          Key use cases
        </h2>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-px bg-border border border-border rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
          <div class="bg-background p-5">
            <p class="font-semibold text-sm text-foreground">Freebie funnel</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Turn a post or story into a lead magnet machine. Deliver guides, checklists, and mini-trainings automatically via DM.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-background p-5">
            <p class="font-semibold text-sm text-foreground">Sales call booking</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Qualify leads through DM and route only the ready-to-buy ones to your calendar. No more discovery calls with people who aren't serious.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-background p-5">
            <p class="font-semibold text-sm text-foreground">Webinar & challenge signups</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Announce a free challenge or live training. Anyone who comments gets a DM with the signup link and a reminder sequence before it starts.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-background p-5">
            <p class="font-semibold text-sm text-foreground">Win-back campaigns</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Re-engage leads who went cold. Send a DM campaign to past inquiries with a new offer, case study, or open spot, and watch some of them convert months later.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      {/* FAQ */}
      <section class="py-14 border-b border-border">
        <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-foreground mb-8">
          FAQ
        </h2>
        <div class="divide-y divide-border" id="faq">
          <div class="faq-item py-4">
            <button type="button" class="faq-trigger w-full flex items-center justify-between text-left gap-4 text-sm font-medium text-foreground">
              How does Botyoo help me get more booked calls without cold outreach?
              <svg class="faq-icon shrink-0 w-4 h-4 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-body hidden pt-3">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Instead of DMing strangers, Botyoo works with warm inbound interest, people who already engaged with your post or story. They opt in by commenting a keyword, and from there the flow qualifies them and drops your booking link only to those who meet your criteria. It's inbound, not outbound.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item py-4">
            <button type="button" class="faq-trigger w-full flex items-center justify-between text-left gap-4 text-sm font-medium text-foreground">
              Can I qualify leads automatically before I ever talk to them?
              <svg class="faq-icon shrink-0 w-4 h-4 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-body hidden pt-3">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Yes. You can build a conditional DM flow with branching logic: ask a question, check their answer, and either send them the booking link or route them to a different nurture path. Only people who self-qualify get the calendar link. Everyone else goes into a slower follow-up sequence.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item py-4">
            <button type="button" class="faq-trigger w-full flex items-center justify-between text-left gap-4 text-sm font-medium text-foreground">
              I sell online courses, is Botyoo useful for that too?
              <svg class="faq-icon shrink-0 w-4 h-4 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-body hidden pt-3">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Definitely. Botyoo is popular with course creators for launch week sequences, build a waitlist from comments, DM everyone on launch day with the enrollment link, and follow up with anyone who clicked but didn't buy. The whole launch funnel runs inside Instagram DMs.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item py-4">
            <button type="button" class="faq-trigger w-full flex items-center justify-between text-left gap-4 text-sm font-medium text-foreground">
              How long does it take to set up a lead gen flow?
              <svg class="faq-icon shrink-0 w-4 h-4 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-body hidden pt-3">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Most coaches have their first flow live in under 10 minutes. Pick a template, customize the message copy, set your keyword, and activate. Botyoo has pre-built flows specifically for coaches, lead magnet delivery, call booking, and follow-up, so you're not starting from scratch.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      {/* Bottom CTA */}
      <section class="py-16 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-start md:items-center justify-between gap-6">
        <div>
          <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">Your next client is already following you.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-1">Set up in under 5 minutes. No credit card needed.</p>
        </div>
        <a
          href="https://app.botyoo.com/dashboard"
          class="shrink-0 inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-foreground text-background px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-foreground/90 transition-colors"
        >
          Start building free →
        </a>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<script>
  document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach((item) => {
    item.querySelector('.faq-trigger')?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const body = item.querySelector('.faq-body')
      const icon = item.querySelector('.faq-icon')
      body?.classList.toggle('hidden')
      icon?.classList.toggle('rotate-180')
    })
  })
</script>
